      • execute

        public void execute(java.lang.String functionName,
                    java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> properties,
                    com.raweng.built.BuiltExtensionCallback callback)
        Use the function to execute a function deployed on Built.io Backend Extension. .
        Parameters:
        functionName - Name of the function that you want to execute.
        properties - HashMap contains properties , property name as key and its respective value as value.
        callback - BuiltExtensionCallback object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Example :
          // 'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
  BuiltExtension extensionObject = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b").extension();

  HashMap<String, Object> propertiesHashMap = new HashMap<String, Object>();
  propertiesHashMap.put("name","raweng");

  extensionObject.execute("hello", propertiesHashMap, new BuiltExtensionCallback() {

      @Override
      public void onCompletion(BuiltResponseType responseType, Object object, BuiltError builtError) {

      }
  });
